item.title: Beginners Anasura
item.dc:creator: tommusdemos
item.content:encoded:
The practice of nurturing mind, body & spirit.

Centered around the notion of physical and emotional balance, Restorative classes are perfect for students looking to alleviate stress and fatigue. Our restorative program includes all necessary equipment.

Our Restorative classes eschew the traditional cultural teachings that surround the practice. Instead, we seek to focus solely on the wellness of students - guiding and coaching them to achieve their goals.

The main benefits of Restorative are:

  • Super relaxing time
  • Class size under 30 people
  • Increase strength
  • Reclaim your vitality

[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_column_text]

Somnus is a contemporary yoga & pilates studio offering professional
instruction to those seeking balance of mind and body.

[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row css=".vc_custom_1449231732620{padding: 0px !important;}"][vc_column width="1/12"][/vc_column][vc_column width="10/12"][somnus_featured_text]

ENLIVEN & ENLIGHTEN

A place to nurture minds, bodies & spirits.

Somnus is a peaceful, contemporary space tucked away among the throng of the St. Kilda foreshore. A space for those who wish to reap the many benefits of yoga and pilates, without the cultural teachings commonly found in many yoga programs across Melbourne.

We focus on keeping class sizes small (under 20 students) to properly coach and instruct students on an individual level. This personal service has become our hallmark and in-turn our classes are often booked well in advance. Our instructors come from a range of backgrounds and disciplines, making Somnus a diverse collective of expertise.

item.title: Valeri Sims
item.dc:creator: tommusdemos
item.content:encoded:
The practice of nurturing mind, body & spirit.

Centered around the notion of physical and emotional balance, Restorative classes are perfect for students looking to alleviate stress and fatigue. Our restorative program includes all necessary equipment.

Our Restorative classes eschew the traditional cultural teachings that surround the practice. Instead, we seek to focus solely on the wellness of students - guiding and coaching them to achieve their goals.

The main benefits of Restorative are:

  • Super relaxing time
  • Class size under 30 people
  • Increase strength
  • Reclaim your vitality
